Jade the Explorer

Switzerland

a serene alpine region

I had the pleasure to visit Interlaken, a central town in the Jungfrau Region of Switzerland that sits between two beautiful crystal, clear, torqouise lakes and surrounded by countless summits. One in particular peak is the Jungfraujoch, the top of Europe, surrounded by glaciers and eternal snow.

3 things Switzerland is famous for

  • The Swiss Army knife
  • Swiss Currency
  • Lindt Chocolate Box
